# Browser support target for the SPA.
#
# Chosen so the modern CSS the theming framework relies on is available in the
# target set: cascade layers (@layer), oklch() colour, color-mix(), typed
# custom properties (@property), and document.adoptedStyleSheets. Engines older
# than this still work — the tokens layer ships static hex fallbacks for the
# default themes, and runtime accent lazy-loading (CSS module scripts) is
# feature-detected with a <link> fallback. See notes/plans/css-overhaul.md.
#
# This is a documentation-of-intent + tooling target (any browserslist-aware
# tool, e.g. a future Lightning CSS / autoprefixer step, reads it). Vite's own
# esbuild transform target is set separately in gui/vite.config.js.

